---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import { SITE, SOCIALS } from "@consts";
---

<PageLayout title="About" description="About me">
  <Container>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="animate font-semibold text-brand-steel/85">
        About
      </div>
      <div class="animate space-y-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-brand-steel/85">So What Is This?</p>
          <p>
            I'm Seej. Hardware engineering by education, systems engineer by training,
            AI enthusiast by interest. I tend to collect skills the way some people collect
            hobbies. Which is also to say I collect hobbies. Photography, watercolor, sketching,
            and whatever else catches my eye.
          </p>
          <p>
            Married, with a mini-Aussie named Momo who has strong opinions about everything.
            Big lover of space and space-adjacent things. This blog is where all of it lands.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-brand-steel/85">Why The Hexagons?</p>
          <p>
            Hexagons tessellate. They fit together perfectly, edge to edge, no gaps, no waste.
            Nature figured this out a long time ago. Honeycombs, basalt columns, compound eyes.
            It's the most efficient way to cover a surface with repeating shapes.
          </p>
          <p>
            My brain works a lot like that. ADHD means interests don't stack neatly in a line.
            They tile outward in every direction, each one connecting to the next in ways that
            aren't always obvious at first. It can look chaotic from the outside. From the inside,
            it feels like coverage. Every weird detour fills in a cell. Nothing is wasted.
          </p>
          <p>
            The hexagon is also a piece of something larger. On its own it's just a shape.
            But place enough of them together and you get a surface, a structure, a pattern
            with real strength. That's the idea here. Each project, post, or obsession is one
            tile in a bigger picture that's still being assembled.
          </p>
          <p>
            Though if you stare at it long enough. Are you sure it's not a black cube?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="text-sm text-brand-sky">Get in touch</p>
          <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {SOCIALS.map(SOCIAL => (
              <li class="flex gap-x-2 text-nowrap">
                <Link href={SOCIAL.HREF} external aria-label={`${SITE.NAME} on ${SOCIAL.NAME}`}>
                  {SOCIAL.NAME}
                </Link>
                {"•"}
              </li>
            ))}
            <li class="line-clamp-1">
              <Link href={`mailto:${SITE.EMAIL}`} aria-label={`Email ${SITE.NAME}`}>
                {SITE.EMAIL}
              </Link>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>
